BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU1889482192
DTSTAMP:20260313T210315Z
SUMMARY:Selichot - Service\, Dinner\, Music!
DESCRIPTION:Welcome in the spirit of the High Holidays with a participatory
 \, music-filled night! Connect with the Shomrei community over dinner\, si
 ng High Holiday melodies\, and have some fun at our jazz dessert reception
 .\n\n**RSVP Required for Dinner and Reception** http://shomrei.org/jazz\n\
 nFree or Suggested Donation:  \n$20 per adult\, $10 per child over 12\, $3
 6 per family\n\n**------------------------------  \nAdults and Kids 8+ (Yo
 unger Kids/Scroll Down)**  \n6:15 - 7:15pm\, Dinner  \nEnjoy a Chicken Sch
 warma\, middle eastern dinner (vegan options available and pasta options f
 or kids) in the Social Hall.  \nrsvp required  \n  \n7:15 - 7:30pm\, Havda
 lah  \nAs Shabbat comes to a close\, children and adults will come togethe
 r to recite Havdalah prayers. We are looking forward to having our childre
 n who are 8 yrs old and up help lead the havdalah candle lighting ceremony
  while reciting prayers with Rabbi Julie.\n\n7:30 - 8:30pm\, Musical Selic
 hot Service (Zamru-Style!)  \nParticipatory\, music-filled service led by 
 Rabbi Julie\, Talia Lakritz\, Suzanna Grobman\, Debra Caplan and accompani
 ed by Oren Neiman and his jazz ensemble.\n\nSelichot_Booklet: https://driv
 e.google.com/file/d/1CfQz_30MYWaFAZKkGfbE57su_JTd1D1O/view?usp=drive_link 
  \nStreaming: http://shomrei.org/live\n\n  \n8:30 - 9:30pm\, Dessert &amp\
 ; Jazz Reception  \nThe party continues with a dessert reception. Live mus
 ic will be provided by the jazz ensemble. We will also ask participants to
  interact with our Selichot art installation by adding your thoughts and w
 ishes to our interactive board.\n\n**------------------------------**\n\n*
 *Kids 7 and Younger**  \n6:15 - 7:15pm\, Little Kid's Dinner &amp\; Hangou
 t (play time)  \n(in the YAC)  \nrsvp required  \n  \n7:15 - 7:30pm\, Havd
 alah  \nAs Shabbat comes to a close\, children and adults will come togeth
 er to sing the Havdalah blessings. We are looking forward to having our ch
 ildren who are 8 yrs old and up lead the havdalah candle lighting ceremony
  while reciting prayers with Rabbi Julie.  \n  \n7:30 - 8:45pm\, Little Ki
 d's Movie &amp\; Selichot Art Project  \nDrop off the little kids\, childc
 are is free. (in classroom 1 &amp\; 2) Children are welcome to make art to
  add to our interactive Selichot art installation.\n\n  \n8:45 - 9:30pm\, 
 Childcare  \nDrop off the little kids\, childcare is free. (in the YAC)  \
 n **------------------------------**\n\n**Have questions? Want to Help out
 ? Contact:** Shomrei Office  \noffice@shomrei.org  \n(973) 746-5031\n\n**W
 hat is Selichot?**  \nThe Hebrew word selichah means “forgiveness.” Th
 e plural form of the word selichah is selichot\, a word traditionally used
  to refer to additional prayers for forgiveness recited during the month o
 f Elul (through Yom Kippur). We gather together on the Saturday night befo
 re Rosh Hashanah to meditate on the capacity for forgiveness and on its po
 wer. In joining together we help each other pray for that blessing – to 
 give it and to receive it.\n\n
LOCATION:Social Hall\, Gallery\, [#]holiday:rosh_hashanah
CATEGORIES:Events
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
