SUMMARY:Family Kabbalat Shabbat
DESCRIPTION:**4:45pm** - Shabbat Sha-Blue-Jeans (families with kids 0-2nd g
 rade) in the **YAC**  \n**5:30pm** - Dinner for all families (including JL
 C age families)  \n**6:30pm** - Family Kabbalat Shabbat (for families and 
 kids ages 2nd grade and older) in the **sanctuary**  \n  \nDinner in the Y
 AC  \n  \n**RSVP for Dinner:** https://shomrei.org/family  \n  \n**Shabbat
  Sha-Blue-Jeans**  \nJoin Rabbi Uri for a spirited and fun Shabbat service
 .  \nWear your jeans and come ready to sing and dance as we welcome Shabba
 t together!  \nOpen to all families with kids in second grade and younger.
   \n(Older siblings are welcome.)  \n  \n**Shabbat Dinner**   \nFamilies a
 re invited to join for dinner\, stay after Shabbat Sha-Blue-Jeans or come 
 for dinner before the JLC Family Service.   \nVoluntary suggested donation
  of $18 per family to offset costs.  \n  \n**Family Kabbalat Shabbat**  \n
 This is a highly participatory Kabbalat Shabbat.   \nGeared towards childr
 en (2nd- 7th grade) and their parents\, grandparents\, and caregivers.  \n
 Led by Rabbi Uri\, Sarah Kamenetsky\, and the students from our JLC (Jewis
 h Learning Center)  \n  \n**Questions?**  \nContact the Shomrei office\, (
 973) 746-5031  \nopen-door@shomrei.org\n\n
