BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU1892966145
DTSTAMP:20260313T210315Z
SUMMARY:Shomrei Gives Back - Mitzvah Day
DESCRIPTION:**2nd Annual Mitzvah Day**  \n  \nGather as a community in serv
 ice to perform mitzvot for our local social action partners\, Israel\, and
  Shomrei itself. All ages welcome! There is a Mitzvah for everyone\, inclu
 ding kids! Babysitting available. Breakfast nosh provided.  \n  \nOpen to 
 Shomrei Community &amp\; Friends.  \n  \n**Participate in any or all activ
 ities:**   \n  \n  \n**DONATE SUPPLIES** Donate items needed to make our M
 itzvot a reality. Visit our online wish list to make a purchase. Make sure
  items are delivered to Shomrei **by April 8.** Drop-offs at Shomrei are w
 elcome. Or\, fund the supplies with a monetary donation. You don't have to
  donate items to participate (but it helps!)  \n**online wish list: https:
 //shomrei.org/wishlist**  \n**alternative monetary donation:** **https://s
 homrei.org/supplies**  \n **VOLUNTEER YOUR TIME**  \nChoose your task when
  you arrive\, among:  \n- Assemble Senior grocery bags for Toni's Kitchen\
 n- Sort donated spring &amp\; summer clothes for Human Needs Food Pantry\n
 - Assemble "Welcome to Your New Home" kits for Family Promise\n- Make sand
 wiches for MESH\n- Garden outdoors at Shomrei\n- Make friendship bracelets
  for a school in Israel (kid-specific)\n- Color pictures/write letters for
  seniors (kid-specific)\n- Write thank you cards for pet adoptions for the
  Montclair Animal Shelter (kid-specific)\n\n  \n**register here: https://s
 homrei.org/mitzvah  \n  \n**PARTICIPATE IN A DRIVE**  \nBring breakfast ce
 reals and/or adult and children’s summer clothing for Human Needs Food P
 antry to Shomrei (Drop off at Shomrei or bring with you on Mitzvah day.)  
 \n  \n**Questions?** Contact Melissa Mehl\,   \nOperations Manager  \nmmeh
 l@shomrei.org  \n(973) 746-5031\,[](http://voice.google.com/calls?a=nc\,%2
 B19737465031) x101\n\n
CATEGORIES:Events
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
