 . Members from Bnai Keshet\, Temple Sholom of West Essex\, Temple Ner Tami
 d\, and Congregation Shomrei Emunah will once again come together to study
  and discuss interesting Jewish topics late into the night. Each year one 
 of our local community synagogues takes a turn as host. **The host this ye
 ar is .**  \n  \n**Guest Scholar:**   \n  \n**Schedule**   \n5:30pm - Youn
 g Families Program (please RSVP: https://www.bnaikeshet.org/bnaikeshet.org
 /shavuot#family for this activity)  \n7:00pm - Pizza dinner for teens  \n7
 :30pm - Festival Maariv Evening Service and Oneg  \n9:00pm - Keynote Addre
 ss  \n10:00pm - Breakout Study Sessions 1  \n11:00pm - Breakout Study Sess
 ions 2   \n12:00am - Reading of the Ten Commandments  \n12:30am - Final Te
 aching from Dr Elsie Stern\n\n
