BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU1985224008
DTSTAMP:20260313T210315Z
SUMMARY:Midday Meetup
DESCRIPTION:A monthly gathering to make connections and learn together.  \n
 11:45am Catered Lunch   \n12:15pm Featured Program   \n  \nPre-registratio
 n encouraged. Walk-ins also welcome.   \nCost: $10 per person for lunch (p
 re-paid or at the door)  \nRSVP: https://shomrei.easyshul.com/events/68f93
 b3e6ca2d800260a6c51  \n  \n**Featured Program** Dr. Tarika Daftary-Kapur i
 n conversation with Shomrei member Audrey Levitin  \n   \nWhat happens whe
 n children sentenced to life in prison are given a second chance and relea
 sed decades later? Join us to explore research conducted by Dr. Tarika Daf
 tary-Kapur that sheds light on their journeys home\, their challenges\, an
 d impact on the community (including public safety). Together\, we’ll co
 nsider what justice\, healing\, and community support look like when young
  people return after years behind bars. Come ready to listen\, reflect\, a
 nd ask questions about what true second chances can mean.  \n  \nAbout Tar
 ika Daftary-Kapur  \nDr. Daftary-Kapur is a nationally renowned legal psyc
 hologist and Professor of Justice Studies at Montclair State University. H
 er expertise is in adolescent decision making and criminal sentencing refo
 rm. She conducted one of the first studies of second look opportunities fo
 r people sentenced to life without parole as children\, and subsequently r
 eleased following a series of Supreme Court rulings.  \n  \nAbout Audrey L
 evitin  \nAudrey Levitin is a Senior Consultant at CauseWired\, a firm wor
 king with human rights and civil liberties organizations. For 15 years\, s
 he was the Director of Development at the Innocence Project. She served as
  Co-Chair of US/Israel Women to Women\, now a project of the National Coun
 cil of Jewish Women. She is an essayist and her work has been seen in the 
 Star Ledger\, The Forward\, MetroWest Jewish Week\, the Blogs of the Times
  of Israel\, and Cape Cod Life.   \n  \nFull_Season_Schedule_for_Midday_Me
 etUps: https://shomrei.org/calendar/midday-meetup-calendar  \n  \n**Questi
 ons?** Contact June Zimmerman\,   \nVP for Programming  \njzimmerman@shomr
 ei.org  \n  \n\\#middaymeetup\n\n
LOCATION:Social Hall
CATEGORIES:Events
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
