UID:TU2005886230
DTSTAMP:20260313T210315Z
SUMMARY:Midday MeetUp - Book Talk with Jennifer Moses
DESCRIPTION:**Midday MeetUp - Book Talk with Jennifer Anne Moses**  \n  \nA
  monthly gathering to make connections and learn together.  \n11:45am Cate
 red Lunch (free)  \n12:30pm Featured Program   \n  \nPre-registration enco
 uraged. Walk-ins also welcome.   \n  \nPlease RSVP so we know how much foo
 d to buy.  \nRSVP: https://shomrei.easyshul.com/events/693853717bcacf00262
 d7335  \n **Featured Program** Rabbi Julie will interview Jennifer about *
 You've Told Me Before*\, her new collection of short stories.  \n  \n**Abo
 ut the Book**  \nIn this short story collection\, Jennifer focuses on Jewi
 sh American characters navigating modern life\, family\, marriage\, and id
 entity with humor and poignancy. The stories explore themes like generatio
 nal divides\, unsatisfying marriages\, and the weight of Jewish history\, 
 featuring flawed but relatable characters dealing with universal emotions 
 like yearning\, loneliness\, and love.   \n  \n*"You’ve Told Me Before* 
 proves\, if proof were needed after her first wonderful foray into this sp
 ecialized literary field\, that Jennifer Anne Moses is a master of the sho
 rt story genre."  \nThe Jerusalem Post (read_the_full_review: http://jpost
 .com/history/article-879295#:~:text=Integral%20to%20her%20vision%20are\,Sh
 e%20achieves%20this%20superbly.)  \n  \n**Books will be available for purc
 hase and signing.**   \n  \nThere will be an additional opportunity to dis
 cuss Jennifer's book at **Shormei Reads\, Monday\, February 9\, 8-9:30pm.*
 *   \n  \nFull_Season_Schedule_for_Midday_MeetUps: https://shomrei.org/cal
 endar/midday-meetup-calendar  \n  \n**Questions?** Contact June Zimmerman\
 ,   \nVP for Programming  \njzimmerman@shomrei.org  \n  \n\\#middaymeetup\
 n\n
