BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TU2025222010
DTSTAMP:20260313T210315Z
SUMMARY:Here All Along: Sarah Hurwitz on Finding Judaism  
DESCRIPTION:**Seth Goodchild Memorial Lecture**  \nReception immediately fo
 llowing  \n  \nRSVP:   \n  \n**About the Program**  \nDuring the final yea
 rs of her tenure in the White House as First Lady Michelle Obama’s head 
 speechwriter\, Sarah reconnected with Judaism and was astonished to discov
 er thousands of years of wisdom from her ancestors about what it means to 
 be human. She found beautiful rituals that honor the past and sanctify the
  present\; wildly diverse conceptions of God\, none of which were a bearde
 d man in the sky\; and guidance on living an ethical life that set a much 
 higher bar for honesty\, generosity\, and basic human decency than she had
  ever thought to set for herself. Sarah shares insights about how the wisd
 om of an ancient tradition can transform our lives today\, inspiring Jews 
 to embrace and celebrate their heritage.   \n  \n**Free Babysitting Availa
 ble**  \nEmail Aviva Arad\, aarad@shomrei.org  \n  \n**\\*Additional parki
 ng is available next door at 73 &amp\; 77 Park Street.**  \n  \n**In Lovin
 g Memory of Seth Goodchild**   \nSeth Goodchild was inspired by trips to I
 srael to convert to Judaism at age 61. To honor his life and legacy\, his 
 friends and family established a fund for Shomrei Emunah to continue and s
 pread his commitment to Judaism for the broader community.\n\n
CATEGORIES:Events
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260426T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260426T170000
CREATED:20260115T234631Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260219T184433Z
URL;VALUE=URI:https://teamup.com/kstx8swyw669kakgqa/events/2025222010
END:VEVENT
