UID:TU2042192175
DTSTAMP:20260313T210315Z
SUMMARY:Cancelled: Midday MeetUp - Stories from Ellis Island
DESCRIPTION:**Midday MeetUp - Stories from Ellis Island  \n  \nA monthly ga
 thering to make connections and learn together.  \n11:45am - Catered Lunch
  (free)  \n12:30pm - Featured Program  \n  \nFred Voss\, a former voluntee
 r tour guide at Ellis Island\, brings compelling photographs and descripti
 ons of the experience of immigrants -- how they were processed\, and what 
 might have prompted a long stay on the island or a return-ticket home.  \n
   \n**Cost:** FREE or Suggested Donation of $10 per person to offset costs
 . (Bill My Account is only open to Shomrei Members)  \n  \n**RSVP:** Requi
 red so we know how much food to buy.  \nhttps://shomrei.easyshul.com/event
 s/6967d6065d529f002697a48f  \n  \n**\\***Members &amp\; PreSchool Families
  should use their fob to access the building.  \n   \nFull_Season_Schedule
 _for_Midday_MeetUps: https://shomrei.org/calendar/midday-meetup-calendar  
 \n  \n**Questions?**  \nContact the Shomrei Office  \noffice@shomrei.org  
 \n(973) 746-5031  \n  \n\\#middaymeetup\n\n
LOCATION:Social Hall
CATEGORIES:Events
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
